Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.27,0:00:03.52,Dates,,0,0,0,,{\fad(450,900)}December 16th (Thu)
Dialogue: 10,0:00:24.50,0:00:27.59,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,The serialization meeting \Nis supposed to start at two.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:31.17,0:00:32.72,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,It's about to start.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:40.10,0:00:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, I'd like to begin the Weekly \NJack December serialization meeting.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:45.73,0:00:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I, Yahagi, will be leading this meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.86,0:00:49.52,Dates,,0,0,0,,{\fad(188,0)\fs26.741\bord2.674\pos(946.667,570.246)}Assistant Chief Editor   {\fs40.111\bord4.011}Yahagi
Dialogue: 10,0:00:50.15,0:00:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We have 13 serialization candidates this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.36,0:00:54.74,Dates,,0,0,0,,{\fad(230,0)\fs26.741\bord2.674\pos(290,574.257)}Assistant Chief Editor   {\fs40.111\bord4.011}Heishi
Dialogue: 10,0:00:52.44,0:00:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(866.667,681.889)}We'll be proceeding in the order in \Nwhich I received the submissions.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:55.20,0:00:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,First up, we have Orihara-sensei's "Tanktop."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.82,0:01:00.37,Dates,,0,0,0,,{\fad(230,0)\fs26.741\bord2.674\pos(208.667,568.241)}Team Leader   {\fs40.111\bord4.011}Nakano
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.82,0:01:00.37,Dates,,0,0,0,,{\fad(230,0)\fs26.741\bord2.674\pos(563.333,207.241)}Team Leader   {\fs40.111\bord4.011}Yoshida
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.82,0:01:00.37,Dates,,0,0,0,,{\fad(230,0)\fs26.741\bord2.674\pos(1016.667,568.241)}Team Leader   {\fs40.111\bord4.011}Aida
Dialogue: 10,0:00:58.42,0:01:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The editor for this one is my group's Uchida.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:01.08,0:01:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The story starts at a public high school in a \Nmetropolitan area where the transfer student,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:03.97,0:01:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,our protagonist Shindo—
Dialogue: 10,0:01:05.17,0:01:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Only those of team leader rank or higher \Nparticipate in the serialization meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.08,0:01:09.21,Dates,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,0)\fs26.741\bord2.674\pos(621,574.592)}Chief Editor   {\fs40.111\bord4.011}Sasaki
Dialogue: 10,0:01:09.79,0:01:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,First, the team leader in charge of the editor for \Na given name describes the story and it's aim.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:16.22,0:01:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,All of the submissions are read \None week prior to the meeting
Dialogue: 10,0:01:19.95,0:01:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and the feedback they were \Ngiven is written on their envelope.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:22.31,0:01:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,After reading the feedback, those present \Nat the meeting discuss the submission.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:26.10,0:01:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So I agree with the feedback that \Nwe should be careful about this one.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:29.27,0:01:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'd like to hear your \Nopinions on this submission.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:32.90,0:01:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,His last series did pretty well, didn't it?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:35.78,0:01:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Compared to his previous works, I think \Nthe readers might find this a bit weak.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:40.08,0:01:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but he's changed the \Nstyle, and it's fairly well done.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:43.66,0:01:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true that it's not bad, but it feels like \Nit's lacking Orihara's usual boldness.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:48.92,0:01:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to agree. It feels like \Nhe's kind of fumbling around.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:59.59,0:02:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This one's a 'No.'
Dialogue: 10,0:02:00.83,0:02:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Have him revise it and we'll consider it again later.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:03.56,0:02:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Each submission is sorted and given \Neither a 'Yes' or a 'No' for serialization.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.89,0:02:16.94,AriNashi,,0,0,0,,{\fs120.333\pos(1153.333,354.315)\blur0.869}No
Dialogue: 10,0:02:08.35,0:02:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(640,696.931)}Those labeled as 'No' are then told to \Neither be re-worked for later consideration,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.60,0:02:16.94,AriNashi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)\fs46.796\pos(813.333,153.759)\blur0.869}Revise
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.23,0:02:16.94,AriNashi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)\fs46.796\pos(533.333,153.759)\blur0.869}One-Shot
Dialogue: 10,0:02:12.43,0:02:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,tested out as a one-shot,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.23,0:02:16.94,AriNashi,,0,0,0,,{\fs46.796\fad(250,0)\pos(260,153.759)\blur0.869}No Good
Dialogue: 10,0:02:14.36,0:02:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,or given a flat out 'no good.'
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.94,0:02:23.91,AriNashi,,0,0,0,,{\fs120.333\pos(106.667,334.259)\blur0.869}Yes
Dialogue: 10,0:02:17.65,0:02:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The 'Yes' submissions become serialized.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.45,0:02:23.91,AriNashi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)\fs50.139\pos(751,81.225)\blur0.869}New Serialization
Dialogue: 10,0:02:20.40,0:02:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the same number of series \Nmust be decided on for cancellation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.70,0:02:23.91,AriNashi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)\fs50.139\pos(757,455.261)\blur0.869}End Serialization
Dialogue: 10,0:02:23.91,0:02:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't do so well in the last questionnaire.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:27.21,0:02:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm worried.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:28.37,0:02:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be alright.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:29.62,0:02:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently, at the most, there \Nare only three new serializations.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:33.25,0:02:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure are carefree.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:34.88,0:02:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:35.92,0:02:37.18,Default-Alt,,0,0,0,,We've been going this long, so—
Dialogue: 10,0:02:36.51,0:02:38.93,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,Not including the most popular series,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:38.93,0:02:43.39,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,even mangakas currently being \Nserialized get worried about these meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.02,0:02:52.02,Ep Titles,,0,0,0,,{\pos(640,464.62)\blur0.334}Yes and No
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.02,0:02:53.82,NiizumaPlate,,0,0,0,,{\frz-5.5\fax0.13\fs46.796\move(533.333,290.806,588,290.806)\blur0.669}Niizuma
Dialogue: 10,0:02:52.52,0:02:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Happy Crow!!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:57.03,0:02:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already started.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:00.74,0:03:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard from Yujiro that there are 13 \Nsubmissions for the meeting this time.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:08.07,0:03:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And it looks like only about two or three \Nof those will be chosen for serialization.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:12.79,0:03:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That sure makes our chances go down, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:14.34,0:03:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are four authors \Nwho've been serialized before.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:17.93,0:03:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if a newcomer were to be chosen, \Nthere'll probably only be one, don't you think?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:21.88,0:03:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,O—Only one?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:24.14,0:03:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,First sunrise!!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.89,0:03:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Explain yourself!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:27.14,0:03:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter who gets serialized, no hard feelings.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:31.31,0:03:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Y—Yeah—
Dialogue: 10,0:03:33.48,0:03:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Next up is "Hideout Door."
Dialogue: 10,0:03:35.11,0:03:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the editor for this one.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:37.41,0:03:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,After considering the "Golden Future Cup" \Nresults, I had them write a serialization name.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:41.57,0:03:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The writer, Aoki, is a third year college student,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:44.13,0:03:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but she has done some one-shots for a shoujo \Nmagazine in a relatively short period of time.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:47.66,0:03:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,She has no problem getting a \Nname-style manuscript done quickly.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:51.33,0:03:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure most of you know the artist, Nakai.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:54.64,0:04:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a veteran assistant who has been supporting Jack from behind the scenes for about 12 years now.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:02.26,0:04:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,His skill and ability to adapt his art style \Nto any story leaves nothing to be desired.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:06.80,0:04:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Personally, I'd like to bring him into the spotlight.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:12.06,0:04:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They are both experienced.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:14.72,0:04:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If they are serialized, they won't lose steam.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:16.77,0:04:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe they are both the \Ntype to continue growing.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:27.08,0:04:31.84,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,I was told to do shounen manga and \Nended up a runner-up in "Story King."
Dialogue: 10,0:04:32.29,0:04:37.38,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,But during the "Golden Future Cup," I felt \Nas if it didn't quite fit and the results were—
Dialogue: 10,0:04:37.38,0:04:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because it's a shounen manga!!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:42.09,0:04:44.27,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,No, I'm sure it'll be fine.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:44.72,0:04:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true that Nakai's art really \Ndoes bring Aoki's world to life.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:49.67,0:04:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though they didn't win the "Golden \NFuture Cup," they got high marks.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:53.68,0:04:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but all three of the entries that \Ndid well in the "Golden Future Cup"
Dialogue: 10,0:04:57.22,0:04:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,are submissions for serialization.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.20,0:05:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to compare it to them.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:01.54,0:05:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have a fantasy story \Nlike this in Jack right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:04.57,0:05:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure we should dismiss it just yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:07.07,0:05:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Mark it as 'Yes' for now.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:09.03,0:05:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:09.78,0:05:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Next up is "Kira Kira."
Dialogue: 10,0:05:13.45,0:05:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I already told you we don't know yet!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:16.04,0:05:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I just can't stop thinking about it.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:18.13,0:05:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll call you as soon as we know, so just wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:21.02,0:05:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright—
Dialogue: 10,0:05:23.01,0:05:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeez.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:24.23,0:05:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you ready?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:25.59,0:05:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:27.09,0:05:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Two-pair, 4's and 10's.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:29.14,0:05:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Three of a kind, Jacks.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:32.27,0:05:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack
Dialogue: 10,0:05:35.52,0:05:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already been two hours.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:37.44,0:05:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It usually takes them about two hours, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:40.61,0:05:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,At the quickest, yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:44.99,0:05:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This is no good.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:46.11,0:05:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't get my mind off it just by playing cards.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:48.87,0:05:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, let's stop.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:53.04,0:05:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be alright, won't we?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:57.75,0:06:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure we did all we could.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:09.26,0:06:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,M—Miyoshi—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.26,0:06:11.30,Cellphone,,0,0,0,,{\frz8\pos(656.667,84.233)\fax0.04\fs40.111\c&HE5E2E4&\blur1.003}Miyoshi Kaya
Dialogue: 10,0:06:13.35,0:06:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Just invite her over already.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:14.85,0:06:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,My heart can't take this.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:16.81,0:06:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That one is a 'No,' then.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:18.00,0:06:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll give it a 'No Good,' then.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:19.50,0:06:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Next up is another one of the \N"Golden Future Cup" entries.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:22.65,0:06:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,"Kiyoshi Knight" by Fukuda Shinta.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:25.12,0:06:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When we ran it as a one-shot \Nbefore, it came in seventh.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:28.00,0:06:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,In the "Golden Future Cup," it has a lot of male \Nsupport, so I think it is well suited for Jack.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:33.63,0:06:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Fukuda is 20 years old, so he's not \Ntoo much older than the readers.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:36.98,0:06:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm sure his ability to write \Ncharacters they can relate with
Dialogue: 10,0:06:38.97,0:06:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,makes this a good candidate for serialization.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:41.46,0:06:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That is what Yujiro had to say.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:44.04,0:06:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,His characters {\i1}do{\i0} stand out.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:46.28,0:06:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I feel like it's the type of story that \Ndoes well as a one-shot, but not as a series.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:51.19,0:06:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The first three chapters all feel exactly the same.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:54.49,0:06:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He's purposely making them feel more like \None-shots to attempt and draw in more of an audience.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:58.48,0:07:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's important to be able to attract \Nas big of an audience as you can.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:01.56,0:07:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if that is the case, they all feel too similar.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:04.69,0:07:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels like he's just relying on his intensity.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:06.82,0:07:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Being intense is a good thing!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:08.69,0:07:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I can understand your concern, but it did well \Nas a one-shot and in the "Golden Future Cup."
Dialogue: 10,0:07:14.08,0:07:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's strongest point is \Ndefinitely the character design.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:17.11,0:07:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Put it down as a 'Yes' for now.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:18.91,0:07:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, let's move on to Arai's "Cheese Okaki."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.33,0:07:22.17,TLNote,,0,0,0,,Note: "Okaki" is mochi that has been cut thin, dried, and then either baked or fried.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:19.46,0:07:21.67,Default-Alt2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"For now," huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:22.38,0:07:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:23.54,0:07:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd help you guys get your minds \Noff the meeting, so I brought some cards!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:27.13,0:07:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanna play?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:29.76,0:07:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:30.68,0:07:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:31.63,0:07:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:33.39,0:07:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,On top of fixing everything \Nwe pointed out last time around,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:35.96,0:07:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I can also say that he has improved \Nhis overall story composition.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:38.85,0:07:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems like it would be easy \Nto adapt to different media.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:41.84,0:07:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If there were one thing I'd want to see, \Nit would be a cooler character design.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:45.57,0:07:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This mellow design does feel \Nlike Arai-sensei's style, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:49.19,0:07:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Put this one down as 'Yes' for now, too.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:50.54,0:07:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:51.57,0:07:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief, we've only looked at seven and \Nyou've already said 'Yes' to four of them.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:55.10,0:07:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The number doesn't matter. \NIf it's interesting, it's a 'Yes'.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:59.37,0:08:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Next up is "Otter #11" by Hiramaru Kazuya.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:03.79,0:08:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the editor for this one.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.13,0:08:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He's my recommended newcomer.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:06.99,0:08:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:08.03,0:08:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well that's sure forward of you.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:09.42,0:08:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the one that got honorable \Nmentions in the recent monthly contest?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:13.73,0:08:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiramaru is 26 years old, but up until \Nnow, he's never really read any manga.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:20.27,0:08:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He picked up an issue of Jack from the luggage \Nrack on a train and thought "I can do this."
Dialogue: 10,0:08:26.31,0:08:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave his letter of resignation \Nto his company the very same day
Dialogue: 10,0:08:28.51,0:08:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and brought in a submission a month later.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:30.53,0:08:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's how we got otters—
Dialogue: 10,0:08:32.24,0:08:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Most manga writers have liked \Nmanga since they were kids
Dialogue: 10,0:08:36.08,0:08:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and got their start from copying the \Ndrawings of their favorite series.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:39.22,0:08:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they start drawing manga after \Nlearning how to do so from books and such.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:44.12,0:08:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Books with that kind of information \Nhave been increasing lately.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:47.44,0:08:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Hiramaru started with one issue of \NJack and no knowledge of things like screentone,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:52.08,0:08:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and through trial and error, \Nbrought in a submission.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:54.80,0:08:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And he's already created characters \Nthat can easily be turned into an anime.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:59.56,0:09:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He did all of this in only one month.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:03.10,0:09:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a genius.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:04.69,0:09:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's true, then we can \Nexpect good things from him,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:07.94,0:09:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but do you really think he \Nshould be serialized so quickly?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.32,0:09:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We would be taking a big risk.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:12.21,0:09:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's interesting.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:14.20,0:09:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The name's good, too.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:15.57,0:09:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a 'Yes.'
Dialogue: 10,0:09:16.46,0:09:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:18.33,0:09:19.58,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,Woah.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:19.58,0:09:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright move on then.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:22.37,0:09:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We have "Shady Detective Trap" by Ashirogi Muto.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:34.34,0:09:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The editor for this one is my group's Hattori.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:37.39,0:09:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a mystery that received good \Nmarks in the "Golden Future Cup."
Dialogue: 10,0:09:40.51,0:09:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that everybody is concerned that they \Nare still second year high school students.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:44.10,0:09:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I'd like to start by saying that they are \Ncapable of doing a series while still attending school.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:48.42,0:09:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your reasoning for that?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:49.94,0:09:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Other than the three chapters \Nsubmitted for this meeting,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:52.82,0:09:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,they also prepared seven \Nmore names for serialization.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:54.94,0:09:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They also completed five 19 page \Nmanuscripts at the pace of one every two weeks.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:59.17,0:10:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And this was all while they were also \Npreparing for the "Golden Future Cup."
Dialogue: 10,0:10:02.20,0:10:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time as the "Golden Future Cup?!"
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.48,0:10:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They never missed a deadline and the quality is \Njust as good as the names submitted for this meeting.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:09.79,0:10:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's some serious determination.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:12.67,0:10:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you guys want to go somewhere?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:15.05,0:10:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure getting out would get your mind off this.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:17.68,0:10:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll call Takagi's cellphone either way, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.72,0:10:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:21.83,0:10:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to get all depressed or \Nexcited in front of a bunch of other people.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:25.47,0:10:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:27.23,0:10:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:31.48,0:10:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,How much of a shot do you have?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:33.69,0:10:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We either get serialized or we don't, so that \Nwould make it a 50-50 chance, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:36.89,0:10:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What?! Are you sure that's how it works?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:38.76,0:10:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'd say we have a 20% chance at best.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:41.40,0:10:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:42.20,0:10:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You already won the "Golden Future Cup!"
Dialogue: 10,0:10:43.58,0:10:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but there were three series that did well.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:48.25,0:10:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you assume only one of those \Nthree gets chosen, that's a 33% chance.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:52.15,0:10:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a sure thing that one of the "Golden \NFuture Cup" winners will be chosen at all,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:55.08,0:10:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,so it might be lower.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:56.70,0:11:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Hattori also kept saying they were \Nworried about us still being in high school.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:00.89,0:11:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That "Crow" guy is a high schooler too, isn't he?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:03.18,0:11:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It should be fine, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:04.47,0:11:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether we get a 'Yes' because \NNiizuma Eiji set a precedent—
Dialogue: 10,0:11:08.10,0:11:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,or whether we get a 'No' because they \Ndon't need another 'genius high schooler'—
Dialogue: 10,0:11:14.61,0:11:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels like you guys are \Ngetting more and more negative—
Dialogue: 10,0:11:17.48,0:11:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we are.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:19.28,0:11:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They only have a little more \Nthan a year left, don't they?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:22.63,0:11:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Is now really the time?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:24.12,0:11:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll have a tough time always \Nbeing compared to Niizuma.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:28.04,0:11:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, Niizuma Eiji is one of the reasons \Nthey want to do this while still in high school.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:35.84,0:11:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If they're this serious, I don't see \Nwhy we shouldn't let them do it.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:38.76,0:11:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think they need to \Npush themselves so hard.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:42.50,0:11:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen them in here quite a \Nbit since they were in junior high.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:46.34,0:11:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Unlike the last guy, Hiramaru, everything \Nthey've done was to become manga writers.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:50.35,0:11:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't feel like newcomers at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:52.70,0:11:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true they've been working hard on \Nnames ever since they were in Next.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:56.73,0:11:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost enough to make you dizzy.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:58.90,0:12:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it takes a lot of knowledge \Nto write a detective series.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:01.78,0:12:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be tough for somebody so young?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:05.29,0:12:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I can see it getting too difficult and turning \Ninto a battle manga somewhere along the line.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:10.64,0:12:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,After reading their first 10 \Nchapters, I have faith in them.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:14.38,0:12:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm still worried, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:16.17,0:12:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They're so young.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:17.46,0:12:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it might be bad to have too much faith in them.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:21.27,0:12:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,However, their first three chapters are interesting.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:26.43,0:12:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a 'Yes.'
Dialogue: 10,0:12:27.89,0:12:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:29.52,0:12:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:33.73,0:12:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That sure was a long smoke break.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:36.36,0:12:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I just can't seem to calm down.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:38.19,0:12:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always like this when they have meetings.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.11,0:12:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Are those the materials you got \Nfrom the assistants yesterday?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:44.11,0:12:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:44.91,0:12:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure are working hard.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:46.41,0:12:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I just can't get my mind off \Nit unless I'm doing something.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:50.17,0:12:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can't focus on reading any of it at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:52.54,0:12:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This time sure is taking a while.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:54.25,0:12:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It sure is.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:56.33,0:12:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet they'll be done soon, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:59.21,0:13:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We have finished reviewing the 13 submissions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.21,0:13:03.38,Sign2,,0,0,0,,{\pos(626.667,431.194)\fax-0.15\fs26.741\frz6\blur0.869\c&H6B5958&}Request
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.21,0:13:03.38,Sign2,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(666.667,514.759)\fax-0.15\fs16.713\frz6\blur0.869\c&H6A5958&}Please remember to turn off the\Nlights before leaving.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:02.36,0:13:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we put seven in the 'Yes' \Ncategory and can't serialize all of them,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:07.85,0:13:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,so let's try and narrow it down.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:11.56,0:13:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hattori sure is something.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:13.27,0:13:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:13.85,0:13:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten names and five manuscripts.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:16.73,0:13:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He sure is serious.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:18.85,0:13:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You managed to bring in quite a find yourself.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:22.08,0:13:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But really, to give up his normal job for manga—
Dialogue: 10,0:13:24.26,0:13:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to get him serialized.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:25.90,0:13:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:26.57,0:13:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiramaru has no attachment \Nto becoming mangaka.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:29.88,0:13:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If he fails, he'll probably just quit.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.29,0:13:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody can read manga.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:34.23,0:13:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can't draw it if you don't have the skill.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:37.37,0:13:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He has the skill.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:39.38,0:13:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,For a person who has the skill \Nto draw manga to not do so—
Dialogue: 10,0:13:42.13,0:13:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,would be a sin.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:45.34,0:13:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure if I'd call that a sin or not,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:48.26,0:13:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but no matter how cool you try to \Nsound, it doesn't quite work in here.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:51.26,0:13:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Still?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:52.68,0:13:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,How long are they gonna take?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:54.68,0:13:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You said they'd be done in two or three hours.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:57.10,0:13:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I said that it {\i1}normally{\i0} takes two or three hours.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:59.65,0:14:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Just sit tight and wait for {\i1}me{\i0} to call {\i1}you{\i0}.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.73,0:14:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you care?!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:02.86,0:14:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not part of the meeting, so \Nyou've got nothing better to do, right?!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:06.07,0:14:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Fukuda, you need to watch \Nthe way you speak to me!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:08.97,0:14:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do manage to actually get serialized, \NI'll start by teaching you some manners.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.79,0:14:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,"If I manage to?"
Dialogue: 10,0:14:14.41,0:14:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell's that supposed to mean?!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:15.95,0:14:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been waiting because I \Nbelieve I'm gonna get serialized!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.58,0:14:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I teach you to use your words properly?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:19.92,0:14:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, I'll teach manners and \Nyou can teach Japanese.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:22.96,0:14:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it really isn't finished yet?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:25.46,0:14:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, just wait a bit longer.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:29.39,0:14:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeez, I'm just as irritated about it as you are.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:34.47,0:14:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanna play cards?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:35.85,0:14:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:37.60,0:14:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It is today, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:39.65,0:14:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:42.06,0:14:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It sure is late.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:45.07,0:14:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if we failed.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:47.03,0:14:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's too hard to give us the bad news.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:50.16,0:14:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think he'd do that to us.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:53.87,0:14:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd tell us right away if we failed.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.37,0:14:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, I'm exhausted.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:58.21,0:15:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,S—Should I make something to eat?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:00.74,0:15:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way I could eat right now!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:03.50,0:15:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to get mad about it—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:06.46,0:15:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:08.88,0:15:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to get serialized.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:11.18,0:15:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I already tested it out as a one-shot \Nand in the "Golden Future Cup."
Dialogue: 10,0:15:14.79,0:15:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This time for sure—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:16.85,0:15:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Serialization—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:19.14,0:15:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,with Aoki.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:24.15,0:15:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This is boring.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:25.86,0:15:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's idea was it to play cards?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:28.15,0:15:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It was yours.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:30.70,0:15:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just stop.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:32.49,0:15:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,They sure are slow.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:34.49,0:15:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.37,0:15:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess that means we've got a chance, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:39.08,0:15:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:40.25,0:15:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If there are a lot of new series, they have to \Ntake longer to choose which series will end.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:44.88,0:15:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:45.90,0:15:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Still doesn't make waiting \Nany easier though, does it?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:49.59,0:15:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,My group, gather at the table over here.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:51.63,0:15:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, you took it.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:52.84,0:15:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,My group, this way.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:54.46,0:15:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, my group—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:58.27,0:15:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:00.81,0:16:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,T—This is Takagi.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:03.19,0:16:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:11.24,0:16:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations—
Dialogue: 10,0:16:12.11,0:16:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,is what he said.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:17.87,0:16:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:20.11,0:16:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Serialization~!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:21.96,0:16:22.92,Default-Alt2,,0,0,0,,Takagi?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:22.92,0:16:23.87,Default-Alt2,,0,0,0,,We're alright!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:23.87,0:16:25.92,Default-Alt,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but you weren't chosen for serialization this time.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:24.08,0:16:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Get off, Miyoshi.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:25.92,0:16:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I failed again?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:26.42,0:16:27.29,Default-Alt2,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:27.29,0:16:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You made it into the final group, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:29.26,0:16:30.13,Default-Alt2,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:30.13,0:16:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There were four new series chosen.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:32.20,0:16:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It really was a tough decision.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:34.39,0:16:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:35.51,0:16:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They liked each chapter individually,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:37.91,0:16:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but they want something with a better \Nfoundation for a continuous manga.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:39.93,0:16:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I kept telling you that we should focus \Nmore on how to keep the story flowing!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:44.14,0:16:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess you did.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:45.48,0:16:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:46.31,0:16:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You did it!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:47.40,0:16:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,"Cheese Okaki" is getting serialized.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:48.94,0:16:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:50.21,0:16:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You really are a genius.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:53.28,0:16:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,For the next serialization meeting?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:55.32,0:16:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.20,0:16:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to explain the particulars \Nwith you, so we should have a—
Dialogue: 10,0:16:59.16,0:17:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but could you give me a little time?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:02.86,0:17:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, sure.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:05.04,0:17:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, I'll contact you again later.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:08.17,0:17:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:11.51,0:17:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, we'll see you tomorrow, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:14.13,0:17:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:16.14,0:17:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:17.22,0:17:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't a dream, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:18.26,0:17:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that hurts so it can't be.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:20.51,0:17:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I just can't stop smiling.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:23.35,0:17:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Saiko.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:25.98,0:17:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:27.18,0:17:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all because of you.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:28.40,0:17:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Shuujin—
Dialogue: 10,0:17:30.86,0:17:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't have gotten here without you, either.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:37.03,0:17:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's keep working hard, partner!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:39.84,0:17:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:40.66,0:17:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:42.19,0:17:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Male bonding sure is nice.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:45.15,0:17:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Mashiro!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:46.12,0:17:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You've gotta tell Miho!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:47.71,0:17:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:48.54,0:17:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait to see her fast reply!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.46,0:17:55.88,Cellphone,,0,0,0,,{\pos(530,116.991)\blur1.003\frz6.8\fax-0.02\fs31.42\c&HA28257&}Mashiro Moritaka
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.46,0:17:55.88,Cellphone,,0,0,0,,{\pos(543.333,171.809)\blur1.003\frz6.6\fax-0.03\fs31.42\c&HAB895E&}Serialization Get!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.46,0:17:55.88,Cellphone,,0,0,0,,{\pos(343.333,451.25)\blur1.337\frz6.9\fax-0.03\fs36.769\c&HA08160&}"Shady Detective Trap" was{\fs10.028}\N \N{\fs36.769}chosen for serialization{\fs10.028}\N \N{\fs36.769}during the meeting today!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:55.88,0:17:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Serialization.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:57.56,0:17:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:00.72,0:18:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You should be talking to Mashiro.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:02.77,0:18:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:03.85,0:18:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:04.60,0:18:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes you can!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:05.85,0:18:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You should at least tell him \Ncongratulations directly at a time like this.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:14.74,0:18:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Miho!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:15.53,0:18:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's Fukuda.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:17.88,0:18:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Why's he calling?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:20.50,0:18:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Ashirogi, congratulations!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:22.24,0:18:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I lost again!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:23.45,0:18:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit, this sucks!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:24.87,0:18:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Y—You mean—
Dialogue: 10,0:18:26.73,0:18:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Nakai and I both lost.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:29.25,0:18:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll make sure to pass the next meeting, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:33.31,0:18:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So don't go getting cancelled, alright?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:36.22,0:18:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd better get popular and wait for me.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:38.18,0:18:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it?!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:39.28,0:18:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We will. Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:42.14,0:18:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's Niizuma.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:44.14,0:18:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ashirogi-sensei, congratulations.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:47.64,0:18:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I promised, I've been waiting for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:51.42,0:18:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm happy you finally made it this far.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:53.69,0:18:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm not going to lose.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:54.69,0:18:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Bam!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:56.29,0:18:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:57.38,0:19:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You are part of the reason \Nwe were able to get serialized.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:00.66,0:19:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll do our best.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:02.95,0:19:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I will as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:04.81,0:19:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, c'mon.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:05.54,0:19:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be nice to be serialized.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:08.43,0:19:09.79,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,A rival, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:09.79,0:19:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:10.96,0:19:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Fukuda!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:11.67,0:19:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's be sure to pass next time!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:14.04,0:19:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a given.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:16.00,0:19:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stand to lose.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:17.42,0:19:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah—
Dialogue: 10,0:19:18.55,0:19:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't keep trying, you're \Ngonna get dumped by Miss Aoki.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:23.14,0:19:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I—It's not like we're going out yet or anything!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:25.81,0:19:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you do like her, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:29.48,0:19:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though Fukuda and Nakai \Ndidn't pass, they were still laughing.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:32.73,0:19:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, those two will get it next time for sure.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:36.57,0:19:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you gotten a reply from Miho yet?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:38.71,0:19:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like she always responds right away.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:40.49,0:19:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,She's probably at work.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:41.36,0:19:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:42.61,0:19:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure she'll message you later.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:44.37,0:19:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's celebrate, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:45.45,0:19:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I go get a cake?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:47.04,0:19:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, can we do that some other time?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:49.29,0:19:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Why?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:54.79,0:19:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Serialization?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:55.75,0:19:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we'd start in Jack next February.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:58.34,0:19:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:59.72,0:20:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And what about school?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:02.03,0:20:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll do both.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.25,0:20:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you say that so easily?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:06.10,0:20:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll show you we can do both.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:07.56,0:20:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I promise.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:11.06,0:20:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Do your best, Moritaka.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:14.77,0:20:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandpa—
Dialogue: 10,0:20:16.48,0:20:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:20.11,0:20:21.12,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,Uncle—
Dialogue: 10,0:20:22.74,0:20:24.36,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,I finally got serialized.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:25.45,0:20:27.21,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,It's taken two years—
Dialogue: 10,0:20:28.04,0:20:29.58,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,And we're still just gamblers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.88,0:20:38.59,Cellphone,,0,0,0,,{\frz9\pos(404,73.537)\blur0.869\fs36.769\c&HE9DFDF&}Messages
Dialogue: 10,0:20:51.02,0:20:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:52.22,0:20:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that all you have to say about it?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:55.23,0:20:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You and your father are both too easy on him.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:58.69,0:20:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say that.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:00.28,0:21:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a result of his hard work.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:01.99,0:21:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Be happy for him.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:03.99,0:21:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,"Men have dreams—"
Dialogue: 10,0:21:04.66,0:21:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,"—that a woman wouldn't understand," right?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:07.28,0:21:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:08.18,0:21:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell him, but only because \Nwomen understand, too.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:14.71,0:21:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:20.80,0:21:23.97,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,Thanks to my uncle, I was able to see my dream.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:28.39,0:21:31.69,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Shuujin, I was able to take the first step.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:35.81,0:21:38.95,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,And even though it's been tough,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:39.94,0:21:42.24,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,I was able to continue forward without giving up—
Dialogue: 10,0:21:46.36,0:21:47.87,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Azuki.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:01.84,0:22:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be doing the drawings \Nand this guy will do the story.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:05.48,0:22:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:06.75,0:22:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:07.68,0:22:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you guys can do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:09.01,0:22:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,S—So, if our manga gets turned into an anime, \Nwe can try and reserve the heroine role for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:14.73,0:22:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? That would be great!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:16.77,0:22:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do my best.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:18.44,0:22:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll become a voice actress \Nand be in your guys' anime.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:22.00,0:22:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This is wonderful.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:27.78,0:22:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If our dreams come true, will you marry me?!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:41.17,0:22:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know this number.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:44.42,0:22:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Mashiro?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:46.01,0:22:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Azuki.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:47.97,0:22:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,H—Hi.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:50.18,0:22:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked Kaya for your number.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:52.97,0:22:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for hanging up on you last time.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:56.35,0:22:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't have been able to talk much anyway.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:59.14,0:23:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Um—
Dialogue: 10,0:23:01.86,0:23:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations—
Dialogue: 10,0:23:03.94,0:23:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,on getting serialized.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:05.53,0:23:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:06.65,0:23:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We're getting closer to our dream.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:11.24,0:23:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:12.37,0:23:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll work even harder to make that dream come true.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:15.60,0:23:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:16.57,0:23:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do my best as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:19.87,0:23:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like I can talk on the phone after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:21.92,0:23:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:23.13,0:23:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:24.09,0:23:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:25.17,0:23:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't think I'd be so happy \Nabout being able to talk to you.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:30.47,0:23:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe that the time will come \Nwhen our dreams come true
Dialogue: 10,0:23:33.82,0:23:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and we can be together forever.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:37.31,0:23:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, me too.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:41.60,0:23:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, we're all ready.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:43.67,0:23:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's have Hattori sit over there.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:45.96,0:23:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so nervous.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:48.00,0:23:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He said we're gonna talk about the \Ncontract, assistants, and some other stuff.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:53.45,0:23:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He's here!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:55.28,0:23:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:55.87,0:23:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulation on your serialization.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:57.66,0:23:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,T—Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:00.41,0:24:01.80,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,Why is there another person?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:02.33,0:24:03.92,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,Is it because we have to sign \Na contract or something?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:04.50,0:24:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The name's Miura. I started at Jack last year.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:06.96,0:24:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:07.88,0:24:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Y—Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:09.46,0:24:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Good afternoon.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:10.34,0:24:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting today, Miura is \Ngoing to be your new editor.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:13.47,0:24:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:15.51,0:24:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,W—Wait, this is where it ends?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.97,0:24:18.47,Next Ep,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1233.333,70.194)\an9\blur0.334\clip(115,68,1247,221)}The\NEditors
Dialogue: 10,0:24:17.64,0:24:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait to see what happens next!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:19.24,0:24:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What kinda guy is this Miura?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:20.48,0:24:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going to happen with our serialization?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.48,0:24:21.98,Next Ep,,0,0,0,,{\pos(86.667,70.194)\blur0.334\clip(39,67,1156,218)}The\NRival
Dialogue: 10,0:24:22.75,0:24:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Please look forward to the \Ncontinuation of our dreams in Season 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.98,0:24:25.48,Next Ep,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1200,70.194)\an9\blur0.334\clip(935,71,1233,222)}An\NOtter?
